woolwash
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a series of pools in a manageable stream where wool could be scoured or sheep washed.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:wash dip, washpool, sheep-wash
Pronunciation:
Notes: wool wash, wool-wash
